    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay fine, but if you look at the actual arguments being made by economists, isn't the consensus that these programs create a 'disincentive to work' trap? it feels like the pro-expansion argument is mostly just based on social ideals rather than real economic data showing it actually helps the labor market.",
